  "summary": {
    "as": "Reported to Senate",
    "asOf": "2023-05-16",
    "date": "2023-10-18T23:35:26Z",
    "text": "Fire Suppression and Response Funding Assurance Act\n\nThis bill sets the federal cost share of fire management assistance at 75% of the eligible cost of such assistance and provides for a state or local government to use such assistance for the predeployment of assets and resources.\n\nThe Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) must complete a rulemaking to provide criteria for the circumstances under which it may recommend that the President increase the federal cost share."
  },
